tronic industries ltd elron headquarters in the azrieli towers in tel aviv type public tase elrn industry medical technology telecommunications clean technology semiconductors information technology founded   years ago  founder uzia galil headquarters haifa israel key people eduardo elsztain chairman ari bronshtein coceo zvika slovin coceo website wwwelroncom elron electronic industries is a technology holding company based in tel aviv israel since  the company has been involved in setting up funding and developing over  companies and is considered one of the foundation stones of the hightech industry in israel the companys sectors of interest include clean technology software semiconductors medical technology telecommunications defence and aerospace today the combined annual revenues of the companies established by elron are approximately  billioncitation needed contents  history  early years  founding elron  first joint venture – elbit computers ltd  founding elscint  growth during the s and s  s  current holdings  former holdings and spinoffs  see also  external links  references historyedit early yearsedit elron was founded in  by uzia galil with the support of dan tolkowsky of the discount investment corporation uzia galil graduated from the technion – israel institute of technology in  and in  joined the israel navy as an officer responsible for maintaining its radio systems in  uzia was sent to study for a masters degree in electrical engineering at purdue university in the united states during his studies in the united states he worked at motorolas research lab and was part of a team that developed of one of the worlds first colour televisions but in  he had to return to israel to complete another  years of service in navy which financed his studies founding elronedit uzia galil short experience working for motorola in the united states exposed him to the technology industry and he decided to establish israels first high tech startup company he started the c